ary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating method and constructor exercise**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to properly exercise `getMethod` and `getConstructor`. For the method class, I have a public class `junit_junit.CollectorSuiteMethodTest` with a method that may return null, which needs valid constant pool references for `junit/framework/Test`. It seems like `getMethod` could return a Method without resolving the return type immediately, but it probably needs to resolve it when called, loading `junit.framework.Test` using `TestCaseClassLoader`. \\n\\nFor the constructor class, I have `junit_junit.CollectorStringConstructorTest`, which needs proper byte code for its super constructor call.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering compilation choices**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to use javac now. The rule says not to compile or run tests, but I might need javac for creating a fixture. It could be safer to avoid that. Instead, I can embed existing class files from build/classes for a native fallback, but if I have a clean checkout without build files, that won't work. Using a base64 constant generated during editing seems fine. I can read the currently built classes for that. However, adding large base64 constants might be overdoing it — let’s check class sizes first.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TGGZzT5amKUIu3QLU7SF9sA4|fc_0ab6febfddb8b3450169f91083e4b881968da054d5c3660366", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "base64 -w0 tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/build/classes/java/test/junit_junit/BaseTestRunnerTest\\$SuiteProvider.class | wc -c && base64 -w0 tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/build/classes/java/test/junit_junit/TestSuiteTest\\$StringConstructorTestCase.class | wc -c"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2425, "output": 1230, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29255, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "times